results.abstract: NASA Admr Webb says 4 recent flights of large unmanned spaceships indicate manned flights soon, US HR subcom hearing; some experts believe flights had mil purpose; Webb holds USSR will continue to have lead in rocket booster capability for yrs to come

headline.main: NEW SOVIET SHOT IS EXPECTED SOON; Webb Says Recent Flights Indicate Test Is Near

results.snippet: WASHINGTON, Aug. 18-- James E. Webb, head of the space agency, has said he believes four recent launchings of large unmanned spacecraft by the Soviet Union "are prepaarations for manned flights shortly to come."

byline.original: By EVERT CLARK Special to The New York Times
